      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NEPTUNITE (11) resumes after showing terrific promise as a juvenile, winning three in a row at this circuit and distance before a 2m second in the Listed Breeders Plate when last seen at Leeton in December. Likely to have developed further with maturity and two trial wins suggest he will be ready to strike first up. AMERIKIN RUNA (10) is another that was last seen in the Breeders Plate when about 4m behind NEPTUNITE but won twice in a row prior, one of those coming at this circuit and distance. Readied with a trial win so look for a good return. HESOURCELEBRITY (7) gets the fitness edge on the top two and could be close to a win after placing in all three starts this time in, last time coming from a similar draw to miss by just over a metre at Bathurst. SNIPERS FIRE (9) has had some tough barriers of late but draws for a nice trail this time and may be ready to show more.",
